irlume (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: re-enroll needed for dark/dim (IR) face login.

    This release removes the IR adapter (its training data was research-only,
    which conflicted with the project's clean, commercially-usable model stack).
    Face profiles enrolled under 0.1.x hold IR templates in the old adapter's
    embedding space, which the new default pipeline no longer matches.

    Bright-light (RGB) face login keeps working, and any mismatch falls back to
    your password as usual, but dark/dim (IR) login stops until you re-enroll:

        irlume enroll

    No data is lost and nothing else is required. The default IR path is now raw
    AuraFace plus per-enrollment on-device calibration, with no bundled weights.

 -- archledger <archledger236@gmail.com>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
